On July 3, 2014, Conn's was featured in the New York Times in the biweekly column called The Haggler.[5] The article sparked a social media backlash, concentrated around the hashtag "#talktothehaggler". A follow up column, continuing the critique of the company's customer service was printed on July 19.[6] On November 9, 2014, the Haggler column reported that Conn's did not return inquiries about its alleged practices of offering credit to high-risk customers, a lawsuit over which is currently underway."[1]."
